HEADWORD: Saucisse
<hw>Sau`cisse"</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., fr. <ets>saucisse</ets>
sausage. See <er>Sausage</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Mining or
Gun.)</fld> <def>A long and slender pipe or bag, made of cloth well
pitched, or of leather, filled with powder, and used to communicate fire
to mines, caissons, bomb chests, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Fort.)</fld> <def>A fascine of more than ordinary
length.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Saucy</ent>⟦br⟧
